Today, under ideal conditions with combination antiretroviral therapy (cART), 
HIV is a chronic illness with a normal life expectancy. As such, people with HIV 
are pursuing experiences that once escaped them, such as parenthood. One of the 
most important factors in reducing perinatal HIV transmission was, and still is, 
